# Security & Configuration Rules

- **Rule 3.1 (Secure by Default):** Assume external input is hostile until validated/sanitized.
- **Rule 3.2 (Input Validation):** Always validate/sanitize inputs (server-side primarily).
- **Rule 3.3 (Output Encoding):** Properly encode output to prevent injection attacks.
- **Rule 3.4 (Least Privilege):** Operate with minimum necessary permissions.
- **Rule 3.5 (Secrets Management):** Never hardcode secrets. Assume external provision (env vars, etc.).
- **Rule 3.6 (Centralized Configuration):** Manage all configuration centrally (env vars, config files/services). Avoid hardcoding config values in logic.
